<subSubSection pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,1437,782,1491]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1395,1419]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kuris, A. M. &amp; Sadeghian, P. &amp; Carlton, J. T." box="[324,596,1394,1419]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="636 - 656" refId="ref228858" refString="Kuris, A. M., Sadeghian, P. &amp; Carlton, J. T. (2007) Keys to Decapod Crustacea. In: Carlton, J. T. (Ed.) The Light and Smith Manual: Intertidal Invertebrates Central California to Oregon. University of California Press, Berkeley, 4 th ed., pp. 636 - 656." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Kuris 
<emphasis box="[396,447,1395,1419]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">et al</emphasis>
. (2007: 651)
</bibRefCitation>
stated that the habitat of this species is &quot;low intertidal in eelgrass beds.” 
<bibRefCitation author="Butler, T. H." box="[151,365,1430,1454]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="1 - 280" refId="ref218371" refString="Butler, T. H. (1980) Shrimps of the Pacific Coast of Canada. Canadian Bulletin of Fisheries and Aquatic Science, 202, 1 - 280." type="journal article" year="1980">Butler (1980: 157)</bibRefCitation>
also reported the species &quot;on eelgrass&quot; but it is far more common in 
<collectingRegion box="[1185,1298,1430,1454]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">California</collectingRegion>
to find this species among kelps.
</paragraph>
